<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-03T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.3 B 1/92: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-03T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September 3,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received September 3—10:07
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. League has received Department’s communication of July 28th regarding
                            decision of the United States not to be a party to Arms Traffic
                            Conference [<hi rend="italic">Convention</hi>] of Saint Germain.
                            Commission on Armaments has decided that our decision constitutes <hi rend="italic">fait nouveau</hi> and that whole question will have to
                            be reconsidered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>